tldr: The user requested to add a database, an admin dashboard, and
  authentication to a sleep questionnaire application based on a Statement of
  Work. The implementation involved updating the database schema, creating API
  routes, and setting up a simple middleware-based authentication system for the
  admin dashboard.
overview: The user's intent was to enhance a sleep questionnaire application by
  integrating a database for response storage, developing an admin dashboard for
  data access, and securing it with an authentication system. The approach
  involved a comprehensive evaluation of the existing codebase against the
  provided SOW. Key decisions included using NeonDB with Prisma for database
  management and opting for a simplified, middleware-based authentication for
  the admin dashboard. The implementation covered updating the demographics
  schema, creating API endpoints for data submission and retrieval (including
  CSV export), and building the admin login and dashboard pages. During the
  process, the authentication system was refined from a custom HMAC-signed
  session to a more streamlined Next.js middleware approach, which provided
  cleaner route protection. Testing confirmed that questionnaire submissions
  were saved, the admin dashboard was accessible after login, and data could be
  viewed and exported.
